<subSubSection id="3135A8EABC6AEA58647CAB0267AB1798" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E5F8FD92E80E0BBA7B6CC28FF1687127" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C9B691AD07E0CCAC0C22723B67E5831" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="D16F681412D083D6FC709F3361C6D65D" authorityName="King &amp; Gamble" authorityYear="1906" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Ardisia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ardisia tetrasepala" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tetrasepala">
<emphasis id="D0D8A03225C32A802D7B58CE4D3052A6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Ardisia tetrasepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its simple and compact inflorescence with corymbose flowers but differs mainly vegetatively in having leaves laxly arranged, longer petioles that are covered with glandular hairs, a chartaceous lamina without marginal secondary veins, surface with scattered stellate hairs near the margin beneath and leaf base obtuse or 
<normalizedToken id="B92F6C0D389B28EB2A546EF1D4243F74" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
cuneate. The corolla lobes are smooth without lepidote scales (vs. lepidote scales present in 
<taxonomicName id="E2A3C5DCE59BBC8BB2BE367305BF2A17" genus="A." lsidName="A. tetrasepala" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="tetrasepala">
<emphasis id="49E67C5BB74D66F08C7059BB975586F1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">A. tetrasepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
